-- Brewers Radio Broadcaster Bob Uecker to Undergo Heart Surgery on Friday
-- Mason Levinson
-- 2010-04-27T21:38:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/brewers-radio-broadcaster-bob-uecker-to-undergo-heart-surgery-on-friday.html

          
          
             Milwaukee Brewers radio broadcaster
Bob Uecker needs heart surgery and will miss 10-12 weeks of the
Major League Baseball season.  
 Uecker, in his 40th season as a Brewers broadcaster, will
have the procedure April 30, the team said in a news release
posted today on its website.  
 The 75-year-old, who won the National Baseball Hall of
Fame’s Ford C. Frick Award for broadcasting in 2003, also has
had a career in television and film. He’s appeared in
commercials and starred in the TV program “Mr. Belvedere” from
1985-1990 as well as three “Major League” movies.  
